label: Study year
notesForOnt: This study was conducted over 5 years and parasitologic data was collected each year.

label: Study arm
definition: Abbreviation refers to randomization group. Villages were randomized into one of four arms and given different treatment regimens. Refer to study page for more detail.
codebookValues: 1=Annual mass drug administration (MDA) with praziquantel and albendazole before the peak transmission season of schistosomiasis (November/December); 2=Annual MDA with praziquantel and albendazole after the peak transmission season of schistosomiasis (March/April), 3= Two yearly treatments before and after peak transmission of schistosomiasis (November/December and March/April), 4=Annual MDA with praziquantel and albendazole before peak transmission of schistosomiasis (November/December), coupled with chemical snail control using niclosamide
notesForOnt: Study villages were randomized into one of four arms and given different treatment regimens.

label: Age group at enrollment
codebookDescription: Generated based on age: 0_4= 0-4 years old, 5_8= 5-8 years old, 9_12= 9 to 12 years old, Teenage= 13 to 17 years, Adult= 18+ years.

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma mansoni eggs in study participant,  based on detection in the stool sample.
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of Schistosoma mansoni eggs in study participant
notesForOnt: This variable gives binary (yes/no) measure of S. mansoni infection in this study participant. If either of the two slides (two preceding variables) had at least 1 egg then the participant is positive for Sm infection. Other binary variables in this dataset were calculated in the same way.

label: Hookworm, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of hookworm eggs in study participant, based on detection in the stool sample
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of hookworm eggs in study participant

label: Ascaris lumbricoides, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of ascaris eggs in study participant,  based on detection in the the stool sample
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of ascaris eggs in study participant

label: Trichuris trichiura, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of trichuris eggs in study participant,  based on detection in the stool sample
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of trichuris eggs in study participant

label: Schistosoma haematobium, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium eggs in study participant,  based on detection the urine sample
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium eggs in study participant
notesForOnt: If 1 or more Sh eggs were found, the participant is positive for Sh.

label: Schistosoma haematobium (per 10 ml), by microcsopy
definition: Number of S. haematobium eggs calculated per 10 ml urine
codebookDescription: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs calculated per 10 ml urine.
notesForOnt: This is the standard infection measure: eggs found per 10 ml urine. This variable is calculated from two collected variables "urine_vol" and "sh_eggs".
